data.text:
This article is about Formables. You may be looking for Missions.

Formables are historical, theoretical, and proposed nations, states, dynasties, unions, kingdoms, and empires, which can be united when a nation or releasable conquers the needed countries, releasables, and/or cities that consist within the unification requirement.

Formables are commonly seen across many matches as they grant the player various modifiers, such as an increase to base stability, in addition to diverse achievements, most notably titles and skins.

Currently, there are 209 available formables in the game, with many considered ones that may be implemented in later updates.

Formable Information

Formable Requirements

To form a new state, the player needs to be:

The required starting country.

At peace, cannot be at war

In control of all required nations/cities.

Cannot form a formable that is mutually exclusive with another. For example, if you are currently the Soviet Union, you cannot subsequently switch to the Russian Empire, and vice versa. All exclusive formables are listed in this page.

A formable can only be formed once per match, meaning the same formable can no longer be unified even if it's by a different country. (For example, if the United States has formed the North American Union, Mexico wouldn't be able to form it, even if it had all the lands it required, should they declare independence.)

Extra Information

Some formables can be formed by a releasable (e.g. the Golden Circle).

Some require a country to conquer a releasable (e.g. Goguryeo).

Some formables need certain cities of land from another country (e.g. Qing Dynasty).

The amount of formables a nation can reunite varies per country, as each sovereign state has a respective quantity of formables they can reunify. (e.g. Antarctica has 0, United States has 1, while Tunisia has 5).

Formable Achievements

Formable Modifiers

Visit main article: Formable Modifiers

Formable Modifiers serve as national modifiers which are automatically implemented to one's nation upon forming a certain formable. Each modifier introduces negatives, advantages, or both, as it revolves around reformations to the economy, expenditures, resource production, technology, military, ideologies, diplomacy, national concepts, and more.

The official document of all formable modifiers can be found here.

Skins

Visit main article: Skins

Skins are military cosmetics in Rise of Nations that customize units depending on the package. Skins are achievable by forming formables or via payment of 250 Robux. Skins are solely used for decorating military units; meaning they are not modifications to adjust a unit’s statistics. This includes required resources, military power (e.g. attack, defense, mobility, etc.), technology, and manufacture costs.

Titles

Visit main article: Titles

Titles are chat name-tags that can be unlocked by forming formable in public servers. Titles do not serve as a mechanic that manipulate the gameplay, as they are rather used for name-tags that appear in the chat. Titles symbolize skill, project intimidation, or a way of showing a favorable title or country.

Stability

Visit main article: Stability

Stability boost will be given to a nation upon forming a certain formable. The value of the stability amount varies in each formable. Additionally, all required countries or cities will be automatically cored to a nation.

Official Discord Role

Visit main article: Official Discord

If the player happens to form every single formable, they are able to unlock the Collector role in the Official Rise of Nations Discord (invite link), by showing staff clear proof with screenshots and/or videos.
